# API Design (clients: web now; mobile + partners later)

Design every endpoint as a stable public contract. Reference: `README.md` → API Standards.

## Versioning
- All routes under `/api/v1`. A shipped contract is frozen.
- Additive changes (new optional field/endpoint) stay in the version. **Breaking changes ⇒ `/api/v2`** — never silently change `v1`.

## Response envelope (always)
- Success: `{ success: true, data, meta: { requestId, timestamp, pagination? } }`
- Error: `{ success: false, error: { code, message, details[] }, meta }`
- `details` is always an array. `requestId` mirrors the `x-request-id` header.
- Build via shared helpers (`ok`, `paginated`, `fail`) — never hand-roll JSON.

## Status codes
200 ok · 201 created · 204 no-content · 400 malformed · 401 unauth · 403 forbidden · 404 not-found · 409 conflict · 422 validation · 429 rate-limited · 500 internal (never leak internals).

## Conventions
- Clients switch on stable `error.code` (catalog in `README.md`), never on human messages.
- List endpoints: paginated (default 20, max 100), `?page&pageSize&sort=-createdAt&<filters>`.
- Money returned as decimal **string** + explicit `currency`. Timestamps ISO-8601 UTC. IDs are UUID strings.
- Side-effecting `POST` (orders, payments) honor the `Idempotency-Key` header.
- Every endpoint is documented via OpenAPI generated from its Zod schemas (served at `/docs`). Docs must never drift from code.
- Default-deny auth: a route is protected unless explicitly public; RBAC + resource ownership enforced.
